    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/creative-industries/CRI/540.html" title="CRI 540 - Marketing the Creative Industries" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRI 540</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Marketing the Creative Industries</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course will be of interest to students who wish either to pursue a career in the Creative Industries or to advance their knowledge of strategic marketing in the context of a challenging, rapidly changing environment.  It will examine the particular demands and techniques of marketing media products - films, TV shows, video games, books, magazines etc. - that are characterized by a short shelf life.  The marketing of creative talent - the packaging and selling of celebrity artists - will be studied in the context of applicable consumption dynamics and changing global mechanisms for the promotion and distribution of creative goods.</div>
	
	
