    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/creative-industries/CRI/600.html" title="CRI 600 - The Creative Process" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRI 600</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">The Creative Process</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">How do creative ideas happen? What is the nature of creativity and how can we foster the creativity of those around us? Drawing on psychological and management theories, students explore creativity as an individualistic process and an output of formal organizations and the synthesis of subconscious thought and rational analysis. Case studies illuminate the creative process in terms of how content creators in the Creative Industries relate to the commercial development of their ideas.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
