    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/creative-industries/CRI/710.html" title="CRI 710 - Creative Industries Research Methodology" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRI 710</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Creative Industries Research Methodology</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">This course asks how information about the Creative Industries can be collected and analyzed. It surveys research methods that are both useful within the Creative Industries and crucial to studying them. We will review information retrieval techniques as well as methods of data collection (audience research; content analysis; critical and textual analysis; surveys; interviews; focus groups etc.). Through practical exercises we will develop the research skills that are required of many careers within the Creative Industries (grant, report and policy brief writing etc.) as well as in advanced graduate degrees.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
