    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/creative-industries/CRI/750.html" title="CRI 750 - Emerging Technologies in Cyberspace" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRI 750</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">Emerging Technologies in Cyberspace</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Emerging digital technologies and online services are challenging and overturning traditional modes of creation, business models, marketing and dissemination in the Creative Industries. At the same time, new opportunities are emerging for the enterprising content creator and creative enterprise. This course explores what is on the horizon and builds students' abilities to recognize and exploit the opportunities of technological change while minimizing the risk these changes pose to established industry and artistic practices.</div>
	
	
		<div class="courseListLength"><span class="courseInfoLabels">Weekly Contact: </span><span class="courseInfoValues">Lecture: 3 hrs. </span></div>
	
	
