    <a href="/content/ryerson/calendar/2020-2021/courses/creative-industries/CRI/860.html" title="CRI 860 - The Big Night" class="courseListCourseLink"><span class="courseListCourseCode">CRI 860</span> - <span class="courseListCourseName">The Big Night</span></a>
    
	
		<div class="courseListDescription">Teams of students propose, budget, finance, market and execute an ambitious event open to the public in a creative industry. Possible events include a film, dance or music festival, theatrical production, record or graphic novel launch or gallery exhibit. With faculty guidance and mentor support, students work with outside artists and content creators and provide a substantive report on the event's impact.</div>
	
	
